dex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book focuses on ethnic and minority communities in urban contexts and the ways in which their cultures are represented in tourism development. It offers a multi-disciplinary approach which draws on examples and case studies of ethnic and minority communities and cultural tourism development from all around the world, including slums in India, favelas in Brazil, Chinatowns in Australia, Jewish quarters in Central and Eastern Europe, ethnic villages in China, the African district of Brussels, the gay quarter in Cape Town and a desert town in Israel. It offers a positive perspective on ethnic and minority cultures and communities at a time when social and political support is lacking in many countries. This book will be a useful resource for those studying and researching cultural and urban tourism, urban planning and development, community studies and urban and cultural geography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCulture and tourismvCase studies. 0aEthnic neighborhoodsvCase studies. 0aTourismxSocial aspectsvCase studies. 4aEthnic minorities & multicultural studies. 4aTourism industry. 4aUrban communities. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Hospitality, Travel & Tourism.2bisacsh  acultural tourism development.  acultural tourism.  aethnic and minority communities.  aethnic and minority cultures.  aethnic tourism.  afavela tourism.  atourism development.  atourism mobilities.  atourism policy.  atourist attractions.  aurban planning and development.  aurban tourism.  avisitor experiences.1 aChowdhary, Nimit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCloquet, Isabelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCo